        <Parent_String>limestone by composition: aggregate type [300011287], limestone by composition [300137624], limestone [300011286], carbonate rock [300011283], sedimentary rock by composition [300011274], sedimentary rock [300011273], rock (inorganic material) [300011692], inorganic material [300010360], materials by composition [300212963], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A coarse-grained limestone composed mainly of cemented pisoliths, which are pea-sized accretionary bodies, often formed of calcium carbonate, that may have been produced by a biochemical algal-encrustation process; pisoliths are larger and less regular in form than oöliths.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000001051/Dictionary of Geological Terms (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Caliza de grano grueso compuesta principalmente de pisolitos cementados, que son cuerpos de acrementación del tamaño de un guisante, a menudo de carbonato de calcio, producidos por un proceso bioquímico de incrustación de algas. Los pisolitos son más grandes y de forma menos regular que los oolitos.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een grofkorrelige kalksteen, hoofdzakelijk samengesteld uit gecementeerde pisolieten (erwtvormige aangroeilichamen), vaak gevormd van calciumcarbonaat, dat geproduceerd kan zijn door een biochemisch algenaanzettingsproces. Pisolieten zijn groter en minder regelmatig van vorm dan oölieten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052486/Philips, Gesteenten, mineralen en fossielen (1992)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種粗顆粒的石灰岩，主要由豆石黏合形成。豆石的大小與豌豆相當，是由碳酸鈣構成的增積組織，可能是在藻類結垢的生化過程中形成。豆石比鮞石大，且形狀較不規則。 </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
